ce:section.ce:para:
Under the optimum experimental conditions mentioned above, the fluorescence spectra of CDs-Co2+ system in the presence of different concentrations of oxalic acid were investigated. As displayed in Fig. 6
                        , the fluorescence intensity of the system increases gradually with the enhancement of oxalic acid. The enhanced fluorescence intensity (ΔF) exhibits a good linear response to the concentration of oxalic acid in the range of 0.5 mg/L to 70 mg/L with the calibration curve ΔF = 1.51c + 1.21 (r = 0.9986, n = 11). The detection limit is 0.288 mg/L calculated at a signal-to-noise ratio of 3. The repeatability of the present method is assessed by 11 parallel determinations of 10 mg/L oxalic acid and the relative standard deviation (RSD) is 0.23 %, suggesting the good precision. Compared with other analytical methods (Table 1
                        ), the proposed method has wider linear detection range or lower detection limit, which are the important foundations for the determination of oxalic acid in real samples.
